6558-0|page=346|year=1987}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Wood1993\">{{cite book |author=John Cunningham Wood|author-link = John Cunningham Wood |title=Karl Marx's economics: critical assessments : second series|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=zoNIh_NYeRwC&pg=PA232|accessdate=16 March 2011|year=1993|publisher=Taylor & Francis|isbn=978-0-415-08711-7|page=232}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"egsbio\">{{cite web|url=http://www.egs.edu/library/karl-marx/biography/ |title=Karl Heinrich Marx \u2013 Biography |publisher=Egs.edu |accessdate=9 March 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100901101839/http://www.egs.edu/library/karl-marx/biography |archivedate=1 September 2010 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"et\">Several authors elucidated this long neglected crucial turn in Marx's theoretical development, such as Ernie Thomson in ''The Discovery of the Materialist Conception of History in the Writings of the Young Karl Marx'', New York, The Edwin Mellen Press, 2004; for a short account see [http://www.lsr-projekt.de/poly/eninnuce.html Max Stirner, a durable dissident]</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"k72\">Karl Marx and Frederick Engels, ''Collected Works Volume 46'' (International Publishers: New York, 1992) p. 72.</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"manifesto\">Marx, K. and Engels, F. (1848).[http://www.marxists.org/archive/marx/works/1848/communist-manifesto/index.htm ''The Communist Manifesto'']</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"plato.stanford.edu\">{{cite book |chapter-url=http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/weber/|title=Max Weber \u2013 Stanford Encyclopaedia of Philosophy|chapter=Max Weber|publisher=Metaphysics Research Lab, Stanford University|year=2017}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"sep\">{{cite book |chapter-url=http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/marx/|title=Karl Marx \u2013 Stanford Encyclopaedia of Philosophy|chapter=Karl Marx|publisher=Metaphysics Research Lab, Stanford University|year=2017}}. First published Tue 26 August 2003; substantive revision Mon 14 June 2010. Retrieved 4 March 2011.</ref>\n\n<ref nam