m: the inner dialogues|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=hRdyY2f8UcUC&pg=PA291|accessdate=9 March 2011|year=1997|publisher=Transaction Publishers|isbn=978-1-56000-945-0|page=291}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"DL-Marx\">Doug Lorimer. Introduction. In {{cite book |author=Karl Marx|title=The Class Struggles in France: From the February Revolution to the Paris Commune|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=xlYfFDJDXewC&pg=PA6|accessdate=9 March 2011|publisher=Resistance Books|isbn=978-1-876646-19-6|page=6}}</ref><ref name=\"Dispatches\">{{Cite book  | last = Karl  | first = Marx  | editor = James Ledbetter  | title = Dispatches for the New York Tribune: Selected Journalism of Karl Marx  | publisher=[[Penguin Books]]  | year = 2007  | isbn = 978-0-14-144192-4}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"DusselMoseley2001\">{{cite book |author1=Enrique D. Dussel|author2=Fred Moseley|title=Towards an unknown Marx: a commentary on the manuscripts of 1861\u201363|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-Ld9fM0DOYQC&pg=PR33|accessdate=9 March 2011|year=2001|publisher=Psychology Press|isbn=978-0-415-21545-9|pages=33\u2013}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Elster1985\">{{cite book |author=Jon Elster|title=Making sense of Marx|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=I14p3dFLerYC&pg=PA217|accessdate=23 April 2011|year=1985|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=978-0-521-29705-9|page=217}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Engels1999\">Doug Lorimer, in {{cite book |author=Friedrich Engels|title=Socialism: utopian and scientific|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_A7P0fL_kYsC&pg=PA34|accessdate=7 March 2011|year=1999|publisher=Resistance Books|isbn=978-0-909196-86-8|pages=34\u201336}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"GeorgeScanlan1975\">{{cite book |author1=Richard T. De George|author2=James Patrick Scanlan|title=Marxism and religion in Eastern Europe: papers presented at the Banff International Slavic Conference, September&nbsp;4\u20137, 1974|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=gO_mQQU8-GIC&pg=PA20|accessdate=16 March 2011|year=1975|publ