\">{{cite book |author=Ronald John Johnston|title=The dictionary of human geography|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0-GxowMfwlkC&pg=PA795%7Caccessdate%3D16+March+2011%7Cyear%3D2000%7Cpublisher%3DWiley-Blackwell%7Cisbn%3D978-0-631-20561-6%7Cpages%3D795%E2%80%93%7D%7D%3C%2Fref%3E|accessdate=16 March 2011|year=2000|publisher=Wiley-Blackwell|isbn=978-0-631-20561-6|page=795}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Karl Marx\">{{cite book |author=Francis Wheen|title=Karl Marx|publisher=W.W. Norton and Company|year=2000|page=173}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Karl Marx:Critique of the Gotha Programme\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.marxists.org/archive/marx/works/1875/gotha/ch04.htm|title=Critique of the Gotha Programme-- IV|website=marxists.org}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"MaltsevN.-93\">{{cite book |author1=Maltsev|author2=Yuri N.|title=Requiem for Marx|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=gx0X4NvNE_gC&pg=PA93|accessdate=9 March 2011|publisher=Ludwig von Mises Institute|isbn=978-1-61016-116-9|pages=93\u201394|year=1993}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Manchester\">{{Cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/461545.stm|title=Marx the millennium's 'greatest thinker' |publisher=BBC News World Online |date=1 October 1999 | accessdate=23 November 2010}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Marx2008\">{{cite book |author=Karl Marx|title=The 18th Brumaire of Louis Bonaparte|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ryOVzGSq0zYC&pg=PA141|accessdate=9 March 2011|year=2008|publisher=Wildside Press LLC|isbn=978-1-4344-6374-6|page=141}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"MarxO'Malley1977\">{{cite book |author1=Karl Marx|author2=Joseph O'Malley|title=Critique of Hegel's 'Philosophy of right'|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=uxg4AAAAIAAJ&pg=PA131|accessdate=23 April 2011|year=1977|publisher=CUP Archive|isbn=978-0-521-29211-5|page=131}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Mehring2003\">{{cite book |author=Franz Mehring|title=Karl Marx: The Story of His Life|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=486z9lE-jdsC&pg=PR19|accessdate=9 March 2011|year=2003|publisher=Psychology Press|isbn=978-0-415-31333-9|pages=19\u201320}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"M\u00e9sz\u00e1ros2006\">{{cite book |author=Istv\u00e1n M\u00e9sz\u00e1ros|title=Marx's Theory of Alienation|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=5lckAQAAIAAJ|accessdate=8 March 2011|year=2006|publisher=Merlin Press|isbn=978-0-85036-554-2|page=96}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Nicolaievsky2007\">{{cite book |author=Boris Nicolaievsky|title=Karl Marx \u2013 Man and Fighter|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=4rbH49xtcpkC&pg=PA192|accessdate=9 March 2011|year=2007|publisher=Read Books|isbn=978-1-4067-2703-6|pages=192\u2013}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Nicolaievsky2007-267\">{{cite book |author=Boris Nicolaievsky|title=Karl Marx \u2013 Man and Fighter|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=4rbH49xtcpkC&pg=PA269|accessdate=9 March 2011|year=2007|publisher=Read Books|isbn=978-1-4067-2703-6|pages=269\u2013}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Ollman1973\">{{cite book |author=Bertell Ollman|title=Alienation: Marx's conception of man in capitalist society|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8Ac4AAAAIAAJ&pg=PA81|accessdate=8 March 2011|year=1973|publisher=CUP Archive|isbn=978-1-001-33135-5|page=81}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">[[#Whe00|Wheen 2001]]. pp. 126\u201327.</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"ReferenceB\">[[#Whe00|Wheen 2001]]. pp. 136\u201337.</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Rockmore2002\">{{cite book |author=Tom Rockmore|title=Marx after Marxism: the philosophy of Karl Marx|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=FkMgeGZuCOwC&pg=PA128|accessdate=9 March 2011|year=2002|publisher=John Wiley and Sons|isbn=978-0-631-23189-9|page=128}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Segrest2002\">{{cite book |author=Mab Segrest|title=Born to belonging: writings on spirit and justice|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=gOmpSMh3y3YC&pg=PA232|accessdate=9 March 2011|year=2002|publisher=Rutgers University Press|isbn=978-0-8135-3101-4|page=232}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Sherman1995\">{{cite book |author=Howard J. Sherman|title=Reinventing marxism|url=https://archive.org/deta