 world''. 2005\n* [[Shlomo Avineri|Avineri, Shlomo]]. ''The Social and Political Thought of Karl Marx'' (Cambridge University Press, 1968) {{ISBN|0-521-09619-7}}\n* [[Kostas Axelos|Axelos, Kostas]]. ''Alienation, Praxis, and Techne in the Thought of Karl Marx'' (translated by Ronald Bruzina, University of Texas Press, 1976).\n* Blackledge, Paul. ''Reflections on the Marxist Theory of History'' (Manchester University Press, 2006)\n* Blackledge, Paul. ''Marxism and Ethics'' (SUNY Press, 2012)\n* Bottomore, Tom, ed. ''A Dictionary of Marxist Thought''. Oxford: Blackwell, 1998.\n* {{Cite book |title= The Revolutionary Ideas of Karl Marx |last=Callinicos |first=Alex |authorlink=Alex Callinicos |year= 2010 |origyear=1983 |publisher=Bookmarks |location=Bloomsbury, London |isbn=978-1-905192-68-7 }}\n* [[Harry Cleaver|Cleaver, Harry]]. ''Reading Capital Politically'' (AK Press, 2000)\n* [[Gerald Cohen|G.A. Cohen]]. ''Karl Marx's Theory of History: A Defence'' (Princeton University Press, 1978) {{ISBN|0-691-07068-7}}\n* [[Andrew Collier (philosopher)|Collier, Andrew]]. ''Marx'' (Oneworld, 2004)\n* [[Hal Draper|Draper, Hal]], ''Karl Marx's Theory of Revolution'' (4 volumes) [[Monthly Review]] Press\n* Duncan, Ronald and [[Colin Wilson|Wilson, Colin]]. (editors) ''Marx Refuted'', (Bath, UK, 1987) {{ISBN|0-906798-71-X}}\n* [[Eagleton, Terry]].  ''Why Marx Was Right''  (New Haven & London: Yale University Press, 2011).\n* [[Ben Fine|Fine, Ben]]. ''Marx's Capital.'' 5th ed. London: Pluto, 2010.\n* [[John Bellamy Foster|Foster, John Bellamy]]. ''Marx's Ecology: Materialism and Nature''. New York: Monthly Review Press, 2000.\n* [[Stephen Jay Gould|Gould, Stephen Jay]]. ''A Darwinian Gentleman at Marx's Funeral \u2013 E. Ray Lankester'', p. 1, Find Articles.com{{cbignore}} (1999)\n* [[David Harvey|Harvey, David]]. ''A Companion to Marx's Capital.'' London: Verso, 2010.\n* Harvey, David. ''The Limits of Capital''. London: Verso, 2006.\n{{Clear}}\n* [[Michel Henry|Henry, Michel]]. ''Marx I'' and ''Marx II''. 1976\n* Holt, Justin P. ''The Social Thought of Karl Marx''. Sage, 2015.\n* Iggers, Georg G. \"Historiography: From Scientific Objectivity to the Postmodern Challenge.\"(Wesleyan University Press, 1997, 2005)\n* [[Leszek Ko\u0142akowski|Ko\u0142akowski, Leszek]]. ''Main Currents of Marxism'' Oxford: Clarendon Press, OUP, 1978\n* Little, Daniel. ''The Scientific Marx'', (University of Minnesota Press, 1986) {{ISBN|0-8166-1505-5}}\n* [[Ernest Mandel|Mandel, Ernest]]. ''Marxist Economic Theory''. New York: Monthly Review Press, 1970.\n* Mandel, Ernest. ''The Formation of the Economic Thought of Karl Marx''. New York: Monthly Review Press, 1977.\n* [[Istv\u00e1n M\u00e9sz\u00e1ros (professor)|M\u00e9sz\u00e1ros, Istv\u00e1n]]. ''Marx's Theory of Alienation'' (The Merlin Press, 1970)\n* Miller, Richard W. ''Analyzing Marx: Morality, Power, and History''. Princeton, N.J: Princeton University Press, 1984.\n* [[Postone, Moishe]]. ''Time, Labour, and Social Domination: A Reinterpretation of Marx's Critical Theory.'' Cambridge [England]: Cambridge University Press, 1993.\n* [[Murray Rothbard|Rothbard, Murray]]. ''An Austrian Perspective on the History of Economic Thought Volume&nbsp;II: Classical Economics'' (Edward Elgar Publishing Ltd., 1995) {{ISBN|0-945466-48-X}}\n* [[Alfredo Saad-Filho|Saad-Filho, Alfredo]]. ''The Value of Marx: Political Economy for Contemporary Capitalism''. London: Routledge, 2002.\n* [[Alfred Schmidt (philosopher)|Schmidt, Alfred]]. ''The Concept of Nature in Marx''. London: NLB, 1971.\n* {{cite journal|last=Seigel|first=J.E.|title=Marx's Early Development: Vocation, Rebellion and Realism|journal=The Journal of Interdisciplinary History|volume=3|issue=3|year=1973|pages=475\u2013508|jstor=202551|doi=10.2307/202551}}\n* Seigel, Jerrold. ''Marx's fate: the shape of a life'' (Princeton University Press, 1978) {{ISBN|0-271-00935-7}}\n* [[Paul Strathern|Strathern, Paul]]. \"Marx in 90 Minutes\", (Ivan R. Dee, 2001)\n* Thomas, Paul. 