ological Notebooks of Karl Marx|editor-last=Krader|editor-first=Lawrence|location=Assen|publisher=Van Gorcum|edition=2|year=1974}}\n* Archive of [https://search.socialhistory.org/Record/ARCH00860 Karl Marx / Friedrich Engels Papers] at the [[International Institute of Social History]]\n* The ''Collected Works'' of Marx and Engels, in English translation and in 50 volumes, are published in London by Lawrence & Wishart and in New York by International Publishers. (These volumes were at one time put online by the [[Marxists Internet Archive]], until the original publishers objected on copyright grounds: {{cite web|url=https://www.marxists.org/archive/marx/works/cw/index.htm|title=Marx/Engels Collected Works|website=[[Marxists Internet Archive]]|accessdate=3 March 2018}}) They are available online and searchable, for purchase or through subscribing libraries, in the \"[https://alexanderstreet.com/products/social-theory Social Theory]\" collection published by [https://alexanderstreet-com.simsrad.net.ocs.mq.edu.au/page/history-imprints Alexander Street Press] in collaboration with the [[University of Chicago]].\n* [https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p003k9jg Marx], BBC Radio 4 discussion with Anthony Grayling, Francis Wheen & Gareth Stedman Jones (''In Our Time'', 14 July 2005)\n* {{PM20|FID=pe/011971}}\n\n{{Karl Marx|state=expanded}}\n{{Navboxes\n|title=Articles related to Karl Marx\n|list1=\n{{Marx/Engels}}\n{{Economics}}\n{{Social and political philosophy}}\n{{Socialism}}\n{{Communism}}\n{{Philosophy of religion}}\n}}\n\n{{Good article}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Marx, Karl}}\n[[Category:Karl Marx| ]]\n[[Category:1818 births]]\n[[Category:1883 deaths]]\n[[Category:19th-century atheists]]\n[[Category:19th-century economists]]\n[[Category:19th-century German philosophers]]\n[[Category:19th-century German writers]]\n[[Category:19th-century historians]]\n[[Category:19th-century journalists]]\n[[Category:19th-century philosophers]]\n[[Category:19th-century Prus